rest_of_day_open: I hope the week goes well, but as of now, I don't see that happening. I received some very upsetting family news, and it's going to weigh on me on top of the state of the world right now. I'll try to work more to take my mind off it all.
critical_positive: We had a good conversation about several topics about movies, books, and work. It was cool to hear about his experiences, both with his career and his experience traveling and involvement with making a movie. He was a good conversationalist and asked lots of questions. We had a good rapport.
critical_negative: I felt like I dominated the conversation. I knew he asked me lots of questions, but I wanted to hear more about him. Sometimes I get wrapped up in something I like that I tend to ramble, so I hope I didn't come across that way too much. It was good overall.

rest_of_day_open: start of week, should go well but it's all up to me.   not too much more to say than that, as writing or talking about it and doing it are two different things and there is limited energies available from which to draw on and invest in either desired intention.
critical_positive: we had large overlap of personal interests.   he was into sci fi, horror and comedy and was writing a novel based on these things.  he was more than half-way through but didn't have the complete feeling that he had finished it, which i can relate to from doing other projects and sort of knowing that I had done something important and signficant, at least not just for me but also yet not completely understanding it's importance or significance yet.
critical_negative: he was a little bit nervous/sad sometimes- perhaps because of the pandemic or perhaps just because it's a writers sort of life.  not sure which, but sometimes he was a bit needy.  i think he was somewhat self aware of this, but i also got the sense he maybe still beat himself up a bit... so having a boundary was somewhat important.
